  "target_response": {
    "text": "Most of the damage maps to the celebration itself. The biggest movers, in order: your HRV of 36 ms is about 15 ms below your 30-day baseline of 51 ms; your resting heart rate of 66 bpm is about 9 bpm above its 30-day baseline of 57 bpm; and sleep was compressed to 5.7 h with a logged 01:50 bedtime. Your journal shows 4 drinks yesterday, and alcohol plus a late night is the classic combination that lines up with exactly this signature — suppressed HRV, elevated pulse, shortened sleep. That's an association from your own log, not a lab verdict, but it fits tightly. The lever for tonight is simple: alcohol-free, ordinary bedtime, and expect the score to climb back over the next day or two rather than instantly.",
